President Barack Obama sent a letter to the Speaker of the House of Representatives and the President of the Senate on December 10, 2016. In the letter, he designated all funding designated by Congress in the Further Continuing and Security Assistance Appropriations Act, 2017 as emergency requirements. This designation was made in accordance with section 4(a) of the Act and section 251(b)(2)(A) of the Balanced Budget and Emergency Deficit Control Act of 1985. The details of this action can be found in the enclosed memorandum from the Director of the Office of Management and Budget.